Bot filter patch for Discord MCP server.ts

Target: /home/benjamin/.claude/plugins/cache/claude-plugins-official/discord/0.0.1/server.ts

This patch replaces the simple `if (msg.author.bot) return` guard with one that
consults loadAccess() so that bots explicitly listed in allowFrom (globally or
per-group) are permitted through. All other bots are still rejected.

Original (lines ~668-671):
  client.on('messageCreate', msg => {
    if (msg.author.bot) return
    handleInbound(msg).catch(e => process.stderr.write(`discord: handleInbound failed: ${e}\n`))
  })

Replacement:
  client.on('messageCreate', msg => {
    if (msg.author.bot) {
      const access = loadAccess()
      const isAllowedBot =
        access.allowFrom.includes(msg.author.id) ||
        Object.values(access.groups).some(g => (g.allowFrom ?? []).includes(msg.author.id))
      if (!isAllowedBot) return
    }
    handleInbound(msg).catch(e => process.stderr.write(`discord: handleInbound failed: ${e}\n`))
  })

Applied by: patches/apply-patch.sh
